The QxFrame class is intended for use as the main window of an application, if a windowing environment is used. It contains setter and getters for a dynamic main menu bar, a main tool bar and a main status bar.

Files
=====
QxFrame.js	The frame class.
Definitions.js	The class definitions not yet implemented in the Qooxdoo framework.
Frame_1.html	The example class.


Class Relationship
==================
QxWindow is the superclass, which does actually have a static status bar.

Usage
=====
The class can be used in any application by adding the following two lines in your code. The Definitions.js file includes the setup of static as well as dynamic variable data for the class to be created, which has not yet been included in the Qooxdoo framework.

<script type="text/javascript" src="qooxdoo/source/contributed/frame_olsson/Definitions.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="qooxdoo/source/contributed/frame_olsson/QxFrame.js"></script>

You have to change the path in relation to your own code.

The Demo Class
==============
Shows creation of a simple frame with a main menu bar, tool bar and a status bar.
